:applyButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Apply Button

Click SELECT to apply changed property values to the current session.

#######################50#########################
:standButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Reset to Standard Button

Click SELECT to return to the default property values.

#######################50#########################
:resetButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Reset Button

Click SELECT to reset the properties back to the last applied values.

##################################################
# 	Color Category
#######################50#########################
:colorCategory:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Color Category

Use the Color options to define colors for windows, data areas, and the workspace. You can also choose a workspace background pattern that displays in the same color as the workspace.

#######################50#########################
:palette:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Palette Color

Select a color from a predefined palette of colors. 

To blend custom colors, click SELECT on the Custom button.

#######################50#########################
:custom:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Custom Color 

Use Custom color to create colors for your desktop. 

There is limited space in the colormap. If you define too many custom colors you will experience colormap flashing. To avoid this, keep the number of custom colors to a minimum.

#######################50#########################
:customChoice:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Color Switch

Use the color switch to toggle between a predefined palette of colors and custom color selection.

#######################50#########################
:colorPatch:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Color Patch

This color square displays the current color.

#######################50#########################
:patternPatch:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Pattern Patch

This square displays the current pattern or color for the workspace background. 

Press MENU on the Pattern abbreviated menu button to display and choose from a selection of patterns and solid colors.

#######################50#########################
:hue:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Hue Slider

Use the Hue slider to determine the hue of a custom color. 

The hue is the essence, or true value, of a color. For example, red and blue are hues.

#######################50#########################
:saturation:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Saturation Slider

Use the Saturation slider to adjust the saturation of a color. 

The saturation is the richness of a color.

#######################50#########################
:brightness:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Brightness Slider

Use the Brightness slider to adjust the brightness of a color. 

The brightness refers to how light or dark the color is.

#######################50#########################
:colorChooser00:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Windows Foreground Color

Use this option to choose the window foreground color.

#######################50#########################
:colorChooser01:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Windows Background Color

Use this option to choose the window background color.

#######################50#########################
:colorChooser02:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Data Foreground Color

Use this option to choose the color of the text in the data areas.

#######################50#########################
:colorChooser03:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Data Background Color

Use this option to choose the color of the background in the data areas.

#######################50#########################
:colorChooser04:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Selection Color

Use this option to choose the color for highlighting text.

To highlight text, SELECT the text using the mouse.

#######################50#########################
:colorChooser05:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Workspace Foreground Color

Use this option to choose the color for the foreground of a pattern used on the workspace background. You can also use this option to choose a solid color for the workspace background.

#######################50#########################
:colorChooser06:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Workspace Background Color 

Use this option to choose the color for the background of a pattern used on the workspace background. You can also use this option for choosing a solid color for the workspace background.

#######################50#########################
:previewDraw:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Preview Window
 
Provides a preview of your current workspace color and font selections. 
 
#######################50#########################
:colorWindows:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Coloring Windows

Use these options to define colors for the foreground and background of windows. 
The window background is the color of the window frame and the control area. The window foreground is the color of the text printed on buttons, as well as captions on the window background.

#######################50#########################
:colorDataAreas:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Coloring Data Areas

Use these options to define colors for the foreground and background of data areas, as well as a text highlight.
 
The data area foreground is the text used in data areas. The data area background is the area on which the text is printed. The selection color is the highlight when you select text.

#######################50#########################
:colorWorkspace:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Coloring the Workspace

Use these options to specify the foreground and background colors for the workspace. You can also define a pattern for the background, if desired. 

Press MENU to display the Pattern abbreviated menu and choose a pattern or color. Solid color options are provided on the first two tiles of the abbreviated menu. 

#######################50#########################
:colorFg:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Foreground Color

Use this option to choose the color for the foreground.
 
Click SELECT on the button to display a palette of predefined colors.

#######################50#########################
:colorBg:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Background Color

Use this option to choose the color for the background.

Click SELECT on the button to display a palette of predefined colors.

#######################50#########################
:selection:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Selection Color

Use this option to choose the color of a text selection, or highlight.


#######################50#########################
:chooserButton:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Palette display button

Displays a palette from which you can select a predefined color. 

To create a custom color, click SELECT on Custom. When the custom palette is displayed, define the hue, saturation and brightness for the color.

#######################50#########################
:pattern:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Patterns

Use this option to choose a pattern or solid color for the workspace background. 
Press MENU on the Pattern abbreviated menu button and choose from the selections.

##################################################
# 	Fonts Category
#######################50#########################
:fontsCategory: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Fonts Category

Use the options in this category to change the characteristics of the fonts on your system.

#######################50#########################
:fontChoices: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Font Choices

Standard - A set of type faces that meet OPEN LOOK requirements for system fonts. These fonts are sans serif.
 
Custom - All the available fonts installed on your system.

#######################50#########################
:fontTypefaces: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Font Typefaces

Displays a list of available typefaces.

To choose a font family for your system, click SELECT on the family name in the list.

#######################50#########################
:fontScale: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Font And Window Scale

Use this option to choose the scale of the OPEN LOOK glyph font and the chosen typeface.
 
The corresponding point sizes are:

Small	10 pt
Medium	12 pt
Large	14 pt
Extra Large  19 pt

#######################50#########################
:fontPreview: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Font Preview
 
Displays a preview window with your current font selections. 

##################################################
# 	Keyboard Category
#######################50#########################
:keyboardCategory: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Keyboard Category

Use the options in this category to change the behavior of your keyboard.

#######################50#########################
:mouseless: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Keyboard Mouse Equivalents

Use this option for access to the keyboard equivalents for mouse operations. You have the following choices:

- Basic Functions
- All Functions
 
#######################50#########################
:keyClick: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Key Click

Use this option to turn key clicking off and on.

#######################50#########################
:repeatKeys: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Repeat Keys

Use this option to turn key repeating off and on.

##################################################
# 	Menus Category
#######################50#########################
:menuCategory: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Menus Category

Use the options in this category to change the settings that affect menu selection.

#######################50#########################
:dragRightDistance: $OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Drag-Right Distance

Specifies how far you must drag the pointer before displaying a submenu. The smaller the number, the sooner the submenu appears.
 
Adjust the slider to specify the number of pixels to drag the pointer before displaying the submenu.
 
#######################50#########################
:selectMousePress:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Left Mouse Press
 
Determines what happens when you click SELECT on a menu button. You have the following choices:
 
Selects Default Item- Shows the default setting for the menu when you press SELECT. The default is executed when you release SELECT.
 
Displays Menu- Displays the menu when you press SELECT.
 
#######################50#########################
:menuAccel:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Keyboard Menu Equivalents

Use this option to activate the menu accelerators. You have the following choices:

- Application and window
- Application only
- None
 
##################################################
#	Programs Menu Category
#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuControlArea:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Programs Menu Category

Use the options in this category to customize the workspace programs submenu.

You can add, delete, and edit entries.
 
#######################50#########################
:scrollingListCaption:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Menu Contents

Displays a list of programs shown in the workspace programs submenu.

#######################50#########################
:labelTextLine:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Label:___

Use this field to enter the name of the program you want to appear in the workspace programs submenu.

#######################50#########################
:commandTextLine:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Command:___

Use this field to enter the command that will execute when you select the program name from the workspace programs submenu.

#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuChange:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Change Button

Accepts changes made in the Label or Command fields for the currently set item in the Menu Contents list. 

Your changes will be lost if you set another item in the list without first clicking SELECT on the Change button.

#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuAdd:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Add Button

Adds a program name to the workspace programs submenu and associates a command with it. 

Entries can only be added to the end of the list.

#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuCut:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Cut Button

Removes the current selection. The selection is saved so it can be moved somewhere else in the list.

#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuCopy:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Copy Button

Saves a copy of the current selection so it can be added somewhere else in the list.

#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuPasteBefore:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Paste Before Button

When an entry has been cut or copied, click SELECT on this button to add the entry "before" the currently selected entry in the list.


#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuPasteAfter:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Paste After Button

When an entry has been cut or copied, click SELECT on this button to add the entry "after" the currently selected entry in the list.

#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuDelete:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Delete Button

Deletes the currently selected entry from the list.

#######################50#########################
:wkspMenuDefault:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Make Default Button

Sets the current item in the list as the default selection when you access the Programs menu.

##################################################
#	Miscellaneous Category
#######################50#########################
:miscCategory:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Miscellaneous Category
 
Use the options in this category to set miscellaneous characteristics for your desktop.

#######################50#########################
:screenSaver:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Screen Saver

Use this option to easily enable or disable the screen saver device.

When set to "Auto", the screen saver will automatically blank your screen after the number of specified minutes. 

To define the number of minutes, click SELECT on Auto and type the desired number of minutes in the minutes field.
 
#######################50#########################
:beep:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Beep
 
Use this option to define one of the following audible (beep) notification signals:
 
Always- Beeps for all applications
 
Notices Only- Only beeps when a notice is displayed
 
Never- Never beeps
 
#######################50#########################
:beepDuration:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Beep Duration

Specifies the duration of the keyboard beep in milliseconds.

#######################50#########################
:setInputArea:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Set Active Window
 
Use this option to set the method for activating the input caret when typing into a window or text field. You have the following choices:
 
Click Mouse- Move the pointer into a window and click SELECT.
 
Move Pointer- Move the pointer into a window.
 
With either setting, you can set a new insert point by clicking SELECT in a text field or pane.
 
#######################50#########################
:iconLocation:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Icon Location

Specifies where the window manager places icons of newly started applications. 

#######################50#########################
:scrollbarPlacement:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Scrollbar Placement

Use this option to specify whether scrollbars are placed to the right or left of panes.

##################################################
#	Mouse Category
#######################50#########################

:mouseCategory:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Mouse Category
 
Use the options in this category to change the behavior of the mouse.
 
#######################50#########################
:scrollbarJumping:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Scrollbar Pointer Jumping
 
Sets the pointer so it follows the moves of the scrollbar elevator.
 
Click SELECT on the check box to set the pointer. To undo the setting, click SELECT on the check box again.
 
#######################50#########################
:popupJumping:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Pop-up Windows Pointer Jumping
 
Sets the pointer so it jumps into pop-up windows when they are displayed.
 
Click SELECT on the check box to set the pointer. To undo the setting, click SELECT on the check box again.
 
#######################50#########################
:multiClickInterval:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Multi-Click Interval
 
Specifies the time, in tenths of a second, that differentiates a double-click from two single clicks.
 
If the time between clicks is longer than the setting, each click is treated as a separate event.
 
#######################50#########################
:acceleration:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Mouse Acceleration

Specifies the speed of the pointer when moved further than the specified threshold.

You can set the acceleration rate using the slider.

#######################50#########################
:threshold:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Mouse Threshold

Specifies how far the pointer must be moved before it is accelerated.

You can set the threshold in pixels by adjusting the slider.
 
#######################50#########################
:buttonMapping:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Mouse Button Order

Specifies whether the mouse buttons are set for left or right handed use.

##################################################
#	Locale Category
#######################50#########################
:localeCategory:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Locale Category
 
Use the options in this category to change language and culture related settings.

#######################50#########################
:basicCaption:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Basic Locale

Specifies a language or culture area.

Press MENU on the abbreviated menu button to choose the language or culture area you want to use in your Workspace.
 
The Basic Locale setting determines the choices and defaults available for Specific Setting entries.

#######################50#########################
:displayCaption:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Display Locale

Specifies the language in which messages, labels, menu items, titles, and help text are shown.
 
Press MENU on the abbreviated menu button to choose a new setting.
 
#######################50#########################
:inputCaption:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Input Locale

Specifies the language used for input.
 
Press MENU on the abbreviated menu button to choose a new setting.

#######################50#########################
:timeCaption:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Time Format

Specifies the format for time and date display.
 
Press MENU on the abbreviated menu button to choose a new setting.
 
#######################50#########################
:numericCaption:$OPENWINHOME/bin/helpopen handbooks/workspace.handbook
Numeric Format

Specifies the format for numeric display.
 
Press MENU on the abbreviated menu button to choose a new setting.
 
